## 5 · Daily Workspace Snapshot

At the start of each conversation, check whether the workspace files are stale
(last updated before today's date). If they are, refresh them automatically
**before** answering the user's first question.

All generated files live in `.jira-history/`. Two naming conventions:

- **Daily files** — no date prefix, always overwritten (e.g. `my-tasks.md`)
- **Snapshots** — date-stamped, never overwritten (e.g. `KEY-249_2026-03-01_1430_transition.md`)

---

### 5a · Role Detection

Check `.jira-workspace.json` in the project root. If missing or `role` is not set,
ask **once** before doing anything else:

> "Before I set up your workspace — what's your role?
> **BA**, **Product Owner**, **Product Manager**, or **Dev / UX**?"

Save their answer immediately:

```json
{ "role": "PO", "name": "Ben" }
```

Never ask again. Read role from this file on every subsequent conversation.

**If a field is missing** from an existing config (e.g. old config without `boards`),
add it silently on next write — don't ask the user to redo setup.

---

### 5b · Workspace Files — Generation & Ownership

All files are generated for **every role** during the daily refresh. The Owner column
indicates which role's morning summary highlights that file and who is the primary
audience for acting on it. Non-owners can still read, query, and reference any file freely.

| File               | Generated | Owner(s) | Contents                                             |
| ------------------ | :-------: | -------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `my-tasks.md`      | All ✓     | All      | Open tasks assigned to this user, grouped by status  |
| `workload.md`      | All ✓     | All      | Counts + today's focus + coming up (from my-tasks)   |
| `sprint.md`        | All ✓     | All      | Full sprint board (managed by `sync`)                |
| `refinement.md`    | All ✓     | BA       | Stories needing AC, flagged for clarification        |
| `sprint-health.md` | All ✓     | PO, PM   | Sprint goal, % done, blocked/at-risk items           |
| `backlog.md`       | All ✓     | PO       | Top 20 prioritised backlog items                     |
| `epics.md`         | All ✓     | PM       | Active epics with child issue counts and progress    |

**Querying non-owned files:** When any user asks about a file they don't own
(e.g. a Dev asking "how's the sprint?" or "what's in the backlog?"), read the
relevant workspace file and answer normally. Don't gate information by role —
the role only determines the morning summary focus and primary tracking responsibility.

